description: The Sexually Transmitted Disease (STD) Morbidity online databases on CDC WONDER contain case reports reported from the 50 United States and D.C., Puerto Rico, Virgin Islands and Guam. The online databases report the number of cases and disease incidence rates by year, state, disease, age, gender of patient, type of STD, and area of report. Data are produced by the U.S. Department of Health and Human Services, Public Health Service, Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC), National Center for HIV/AIDS, viral Hepatitis, STD and TB Prevention (NCHHSTP).

publisher.name: Centers for Disease Control and Prevention, Department of Health & Human Services

title: CDC WONDER: Sexually Transmitted Disease (STD) Morbidity
